        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 13 at 6:27PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 627 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Ball Flat, or near Piedmont, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Piedmont, Centre, Cedar Bluff, Centre Municipal Airport, Forney,
Tennala, Pleasant Gap, Eastern Weiss Lake, Moshat, Ball Flat, Coloma,
Fullerton, Spring Garden, Knightens Crossroads, Howells Crossroads,
Borden Springs, Reaves, and Waterhouse.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
